Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Olympic Black Power Statue (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the sprinter Peter Norman requested that he be left off the Olympic Black Power Statue (pictured) so that others could stand in his place?

entry.title: Great Martyrdom of Edo (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a Japanese samurai was beatified by Pope Benedict XVI, nearly 400 years after his execution during the Great Martyrdom of Edo?

entry.title: Battle of Dollar (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Picts disappeared from the historical record after the devastation suffered following the Battle of Dollar?

entry.title: a Wisconsin radio station (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the operators of a Wisconsin radio station received unsolicited checks and food deliveries?

entry.title: Adam Parry (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the classicist Adam Parry said that he had only ever considered three careers: academia, law and beachcombing?

entry.title: one of Charles Wesley's hymns (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Isaac Watts, the "father of English hymnody", described one of Charles Wesley's hymns as "worth all the verses he himself had written"?

entry.title: a Buddhist android preacher (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a Buddhist android preacher regularly gives sermons on the Heart Sutra?

entry.title: Nabisco Shredded Wheat Factory (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Nabisco Shredded Wheat Factory was used as a marketing tool, with an image of the factory on every cereal packet it produced until 1960?

entry.title: Bills (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Bills plays for the Bills?
